<div id="wikihead"><h2><a href="http://rephial.org/wiki/UserManual">UserManual</a> &gt; InternetResources</h2></div>

<div id="wikicontent"><div class="page"><h3 id="s1_1">Major resources</h3><dl><dt><a href="http://rephial.org/">rephial.org</a><dd>The current home of Angband development - including bug tracking systems and downloads, user manual wiki, etc..<dt><a class="extlink" href="http://groups.google.com/group/rec.games.roguelike.angband">rec.games.roguelike.angband</a><dd>The Angband Newsgroup. Lots of friendly people. You may post character dumps there and ask for and offer advice.</dl><p><a class="extlink" href="http://angband.oook.cz/">Angband at oook.cz</a>: The major Angband website, including news, discussion, information, and various nifty utilities. Go to the Ladder to see the top scores for many variants of Angband. Includes:<dl><dt><a class="extlink" href="http://angband.oook.cz/forum/">Angband Forums at angband.oook.cz</a><dd>Discussion forums to complement the newsgroup - another place for discussion and advice.</dl><h3 id="s1_2">Minor resources</h3><dl><dt><a class="extlink" href="http://www.thangorodrim.net/">Thangorodrim</a><dd>The official Angband site prior to rephial.org; although now dormant, it is still live, and is the largest clearinghouse of Angband and Angband variant information on the Internet. Has more than enough links to keep you busy.<dt><a class="extlink" href="http://ftp.sunet.se/pub/games/Angband/">SUNET&#39;s Angband file index</a><dd>The largest repository of Angband files (somewhat dated)<dt><a href="http://ajps.mine.nu/angband/code">http://ajps.mine.nu/angband/code</a><dd>Put a code on the bottom of your posts that describes exactly how you play Angband. Lots of fun.<dt><a class="extlink" href="http://www.mirc.com/">mIRC</a><dd>If you like interactive chat, there is a channel dedicated to Angband. Go to this link, download mIRC, and use it to connect to one of the WorldIRC servers (note: you do have to use a WorldIRC server). Then join the channel #angband. You&#39;ll know you&#39;ve got it right when you see other people (the channel is always occupied).</dl></div></div>

